Local businessman, Rotarian and community leader, Charlie Panday, recently donated medical equipment to Khanya Hospice based in Umkomaas, South Coast. Khanya Hospice CEO, Neil McDonald, said he believes these medical suppliers will be instrumental to the centre as their patients are living with different health conditions. Aryan Benevolent Home (ABH), situated in Chatsworth, also received medical equipment from the good Samaritan.